        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 8:28PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 828 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Mount Hebron, or 30 miles south of Klamath Falls,
moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tulelake, Dorris, and Lower Klamath Wildlife Refuge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
